        "description": "<p>A widget that shows a section of comment text along with the author name.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Show extended comment information</li>\n<li>Configure the number of comments used</li>\n<li>Exclude certain authors from the list (such as yourself)</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<p>The plugin is simple to install:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download <code>extended-comments-widget.zip</code></li>\n<li>Unzip</li>\n<li>Upload html-purified directory to your <code>/wp-content/plugins</code> directory</li>\n<li>Go to the plugin management page and enable the plugin</li>\n<li>Add the widget to your blog via the Appearance =&gt; Widgets menu</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You can find full details of installing a plugin on the <a href=\"http://urbangiraffe.com/articles/how-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">plugin installation page</a>.</p>\n",
